{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χῠδαῖος</b>, ον, <br /> (χέω) <b>poured out in streams, abundant,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.1.7 \">LXX</a>]; στέφανοι, i.e. χύδην πεπλεγμένοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 15.686a \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-ως</b> <b>pell-mell,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Hermes Trismegistus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 1.49.68. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>common, ordinary,</b> φοίνικες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 5.31, compare 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “Historia Naturalis” 13.46; λίθος 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.85f; ἔλαιον “Hippiatrica” 69. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> of persons, χ. πλῆθος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.2.8; ὁ χ. 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 4.18; οἱ χ. 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 3.1.5, 1st-2nd c.AD: Philo Byblius Historicus 5, 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “adversus Christianos - Abh. Berl. Akad.” 63 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; opposed to οἱ σοφοί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ ποιημάτων” 5.23, compare “Rh.” 2.157S., +others: _comparative_ οἱ χυδαιότεροι (misspelt χυδεώτεροι) Scholia 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 948. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>common, vulgar, coarse,</b> λαλιά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 14.7.8; χυδαῖα καὶ φαῦλα 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Mus.” p.95K. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9763","accentedUnicode":"χυδαῖος","shortDef":"extensive","mediumDef":"extensive","stepGloss":"extensive","stepTransliteration":"chudaios","_step_Ty